'''Vorposten Peak''' ({{coord|71|25|S|15|31|E|}}) is an isolated peak (1,670 m) about 25 miles northeast of the [[Payer Mountains]] in central [[Queen Maud Land]]. This feature was discovered by the [[Third German Antarctic Expedition]] (1938â1939), led by Capt. [[Alfred Ritscher]], and named Vorposten (the outpost) because of its location at the eastern extremity of the area explored by the German expedition.

